Description: Outdoor gas-powered professional style kart racing.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Kart Circuit Autobahn (KCA) is an extension of (ACC) — the Midwest’s premier motorsports complex less than an hour west of Chicago. While karting has been a staple at ACC for members, the popularity of the sport prompted us to build a dedicated public track to accommodate young adults 14+, adults, competition karting leagues, and corporate events. The brand-new Karting Circuit venue is now open. Just as we’ve done with Autobahn Country Club, we’ve built a facility that’s second to none, engineering it for fun, speed and safety. Unlike at indoor tracks with short runs and low speeds, you can really cut loose (up to 55mph!) on this professionally designed circuit. Grab one of our 25 state-of-the-art, gas-powered CRG Centurion karts and test your skill our .521-mile-long track. Unlike conventional go-karting with short runs and low speeds, KCA features gas-powered CRG Centurion karts on a professionally designed circuit. The Centurion karts, which exemplify the renowned tradition of Italian racing design, utilize cutting edge technology to offer both a fast and safe racing experience. The .52-mile professional grade kart track at KCA allows drivers to burn up the road at speeds up to 55 mph. Drivers can test their skills on a course designed for both safety and fun with numerous twists and turns, fourteen feet of elevation change, and a 650-foot straightaway.

Description: Clothbound is a mobile platform for job search and hiring in the restaurant industry.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Clothbound is a job search, recruiting, and workforce development platform for the most important industry in America - the restaurant industry. The restaurant industry? Yes! Here’s why... Digitization, globalization, and urbanization all contribute to the industry becoming one the largest and most durable employment engines in the country. We can’t eat megabytes of data or go out to eat online, and it’s hard to offshore, outsource or automate restaurant work. Amazon’s rise means traditional ground floor retail is being replaced by restaurants with increased frequency. Data to back this up shows 10% of employable people in the US work in the industry. Restaurants now account for 50% of every food dollar spent. 2015 will be the first year restaurant spending exceeds grocery spending. We’ve built a 2-sided, mobile marketplace where restaurants can directly access, search, and recruit candidates. Candidates can create professional profiles, view jobs, assess quality of employers, interact with hirers, and apply for positions or be recruited by our restaurants through the platform.  Successful restaurant employment and hiring prioritizes personality and soft skill before experience and technical ability. We inverted the traditional resume to create candidate profiles focusing on personality, interest, and preferred work environment followed by work experience and education. Restaurants in turn answer what is compelling about working for them before adding key information about position, location, etc. We’ve then built an intuitive system to power automated matching of candidates and employers. Clothbound users can tell the app exactly what they are looking for in their next job/employee, instantly view the results, take their desired action, and save the search to receive automatic updates as new matches become available. For restaurants, Clothbound reduces the time and cost to hire, and leads to better job fit and reduced turnover. For candidates, Clothbound provides a simple, yet powerful tool for finding the right restaurant job and getting hired.
Industry Groups: Administrative Services, Apps, Food and Beverage, Internet Services, Professional Services, Software
